        "content": "<p>Hey guys, </p>\n<p>Is there a definition like the following in mathlib?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CartesianProduct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">)}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Basically I'd like to work with Cartesian Products in the context of proving various set theory lemmas like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CartesianProduct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CartesianProduct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CartesianProduct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which won't work with <code>Prod</code> naturally because <code>Prod</code> and <code>Set α</code> are different types.</p>\n<p>And is there a file with Cartesian Product lemmas in mathlib? Things like <code>A × (B ∩ C) = (A × B) ∩ (A × C)</code>?</p>",
